'''RÃ©my Riou''' (born 6 August 1987 in [[Lyon]]) is a [[France|French]] [[Association football|football]] [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] who plays for [[Toulouse FC|Toulouse]].
He was a member [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]]'s first team since 2003, but failed to make his Ligue 1 debut for the club and moved to [[FC Lorient|Lorient]] on a one-season loan in July 2006. He made his Ligue 1 debut on 4 November 2006 in the Lorient's 1â0 away victory over [[Olympique de Marseille]]. In July 2007, he moved to [[AJ Auxerre|Auxerre]] on a four-year contract, making his Ligue 1 debut for the club on 18 August 2007 in their 1â0 home victory over [[SM Caen|Caen]].
